Just to let everyone know, there is or can be a form of tablature for every insturment that involves fingerings except perhaps keyboards.  When I played trumpet in hight elementary school, there were little pictures with three circles-open indicating valve up, closed indicating valve down-over the notes in the front of the beginner's book.  Reeds had a row of 10 or 11 smaller circles-10 in a row and one of to the side for the octave key.
Once the music got to even quarter notes, the tab was to slow to use--but if one accidental came along, I imagine it could help.

I knew of players wo would write the fingering in above the noes in varios scales-a form of tab.

Al

